      • checkValidUsers

        private static void checkValidUsers(Users users,
                                    Stocks stocks)
                             throws java.io.IOException
        This method checks whether the Users unmarshalled are valid or not.

        Note: this must be invoked only after the checkValidStocks(Stocks) has been invoked on the given Stocks, and determined them as valid.

        Parameters:
        users - the Users to check for validity.
        stocks - the Stocks to compare each Users Holdings validity with.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the users are invalid.
